{"key":"post-10851518","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10851518</id>\n<content>Yes.&amp;nbsp; If it's crunchy and doesn't absorb like a sponge, it's not a verm substitute.&amp;nbsp; It should work as a Perlite substitute since it will 'hold' water and then evaporate it out as moisture for humidity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Go ahead and make some BRF cakes with coir instead of verm.&amp;nbsp; They'll fruit but not as well.&amp;nbsp; In the meantime, order some filter material for 1 liter jars and move to grains on future grows.&amp;nbsp; You'll need a pressure cooker for the grains and a source of horse or cow manure to spawn them to later.&amp;nbsp; You can find text and sample video clips on my website linked below to most of what you need.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10851545</next>\n<prev>10851421</prev>\n<first>10850962</first>\n<last>10875477</last>\n<when>1250175968</when>\n<utime>08/13/09 06:06 PM</utime>\n</post>"}